2. Physical activity levels were measured during the study.
3. The study included a centre-based group.
4. The study included a home-based group.
5. The physical activity levels in the centre-based group did not change during the study.
6. The p-value for the centre-based group was 0.38.
7. The physical activity levels in the home-based group did not change during the study.
8. The p-value for the home-based group was 0.80.
